Jihohi 18 da D.C. sun goyi bayan kalubalen sabuwar manufar neman mafaka
Jihohi 18 da Gundumar Columbia na goyon bayan kalubalen shari'a ga sabuwar manufar Amurka da ke hana mafaka ga wadanda suka tsere daga 'yan bindiga ko tashin hankali na cikin gida.
Wakilan jihohi 18 da gundumar sun gabatar da takardar abokantaka da kotu a ranar Juma'a a Washington don tallafawa mai neman mafaka da ke kalubalantar manufofin, NBC News ta ruwaito.
Ba a bayyana cikakken sunan mai shigar da kara a cikin karar Grace v. Sessions da Kungiyar 'Yancin Jama'a ta Amurka ta shigar a watan Agusta ba game da manufofin tarayya.
Ta ce abokin aikinta "da 'ya'yansa maza masu aikata mugunta, " sun yi mata fyade amma jami'an Amurka sun ki amincewa da bukatar ta na neman mafaka a ranar 20 ga watan Yuli.
An tsare ta a Texas.
Lauyoyin jihohin da ke goyon bayan Grace sun bayyana El Salvador, Honduras da Guatemala, waɗanda ke samar da adadi mai yawa na masu neman mafaka a Amurka, a matsayin ƙasashe da ke fuskantar matsaloli masu yawa tare da ƙungiyoyi da tashin hankali na cikin gida.
Sabuwar manufar mafaka ta Amurka ta soke shawarar da Hukumar Daukaka Kara ta Baƙi ta yanke a shekarar 2014 wacce ta ba da damar baƙi marasa izini da ke tserewa daga tashin hankali na cikin gida su nemi mafaka.
Babban lauyan gundumar Columbia Karl Racine ya ce a cikin wata sanarwa ranar Juma'a cewa sabuwar manufar "ta yi watsi da shekarun da suka gabata na dokokin jihohi, tarayya, da na kasa da kasa".
"Dokar tarayya ta bukaci cewa a yanke hukunci a kan dukkan bukatar neman mafaka bisa ga takamaiman gaskiya da kuma yanayin da ake bukata, kuma irin wannan haramcin ya saba wa wannan ka'ida", in ji takardar abokinsa.
Lauyoyi sun kara da cewa a cikin takardar cewa manufar hana baƙi shiga tana cutar da tattalin arzikin Amurka, suna cewa suna iya zama 'yan kasuwa da "samar da aikin da ake buƙata".
Babban lauya Jeff Sessions ya umarci alƙalan shige da fice da su daina ba da mafaka ga waɗanda suka tsere daga cin zarafin gida da tashin hankali a watan Yuni.
